<HEAD>Romania's 11-Day Revolution</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Romania, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Key events in the <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION>'s popular uprising:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Dec. 15 _ Demonstrators ring a chuch in <LOCATION> Timisoara </LOCATION>, in western <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION>, to prevent security forces from arresting a dissident clergyman who was active in promoting the rights of ethnic Hungarians.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Dec. 16-17 _ Security forces open fire on thousands of demonstators in <LOCATION> Timisoara </LOCATION>, who have expanded their protest to demand freedom and a better life. Hundreds are buried in mass graves.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Dec. 18 _ The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> issues a formal protest over the use of force in <LOCATION> Timisoara </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Dec. 19 _ More shooting is reported in <LOCATION> Timisoara </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>'s parliament and Soviet Foreign Minister <PERSON> Eduard </PERSON> <PERSON> Shevardnadze </PERSON> condemn the violence.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Wednesday _ President <PERSON> Nicolae </PERSON> <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON>, returning from a state visit to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, declares a state of emergency in western <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION> and blames the unrest on `` facist, reactionary groups.'' Protests spread to at least eight other cities and in <LOCATION> Timisoara </LOCATION> tens of thousands of people take to the streets, chanting `` Give us our dead!''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Thursday _ The revolution spreads to the capital, and security forces open fire on protesters. <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON> is shouted down while addressing what he had planned as an orchestrated rally. State television shows his shocked face.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Friday _ <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> units join the rebellion, and a group known as the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Salvation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> announces it has overthown <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON> and will form a provincial government. It says it will try leaders of his 24-year-old regime and restore democracy. <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON> and his wife, <PERSON> Elena </PERSON>, flee the presidential palace by helicopter. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and European nations applaud his ouster.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Saturday _ The provisional government says the <ORGANIZATION> Ceausescus </ORGANIZATION> are captured in a town north of <LOCATION> Bucharest </LOCATION>. Savage street fighting takes place between the army, which backs to the new government, and elements of the hated secret police, loyal to <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON>.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Sunday _ Fierce street fighting continues in the capital and other cities.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Monday _ State radio announces the execution of <PERSON> Ceausescu </PERSON> and his wife after a secret trial that found them guilty of genocide and plundering more than $ 1 billion. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> and other major powers recognize the provisional government. Romanians openly celebrate their first Christmas in four decades.
</TEXT>
