<SECOND>PM-Panama-Cheney,0494</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cheney Confirms `Stealth' Planes Dropped Bombs On Panama</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Panama, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DORALISA PILARTE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>QUARRY HEIGHTS, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Advanced-technology `` stealth'' jets slipped through Panamanian air defenses and dropped two 2,000-pound bombs on a military base in the early hours of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> invasion, said <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Cheney </PERSON>. <PERSON> Cheney </PERSON> told a Monday news conference in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> that the raid before dawn Wednesday was intended to `` stun and disorient'' the Panamanian Defense Forces at <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hato </LOCATION> before airborne troops were dropped there. The troops attacked an officers' school and base of the <ORGANIZATION> Machos </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> de </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Monte </ORGANIZATION> battalion, one of deposed Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s crack units The raid, first reported by a <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> spokesman on Saturday, was the first combat use of the F-117A fighter jet that employs `` stealth'' technology designed to elude radar. To date, the super-secret fighter built by the <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has been kept from public viewing, with a squadron based in <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION>. A photograph of the plane released by the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> last year depicts a relatively small swept-wing plane with a flat underbelly. From some angles it looks like a stingray. Stealth technology makes extensive use of exotic composite materials, some of which absorb rather than reflect radar waves, and avoids sharp surface angles. <LOCATION> Cheney </LOCATION> refused to elaborate on negotiations over <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, who is wanted in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> on drug trafficking charges. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> sought refuge Sunday in the <ORGANIZATION> Vatican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORG