nd <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> guerrilla factions allied with <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION> to attack the Israeli-held zone. Also Tuesday, police said heavy artillery duels raged Tuesday in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> about 15 miles west of <LOCATION> Nabi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Safa </LOCATION> between the Iranian-backed <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>, or Party of God, and the Syrian-allied Amal. The two militias also clashed with machine guns and rocket-propelled grenades in the Shiite slums of <LOCATION> Hay </LOCATION> <LOCATION> el-Lija </LOCATION> in west <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> after midday. There were no reports of casualties in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>. Police have reported at least 38 people killed and 150 wounded in the south since Saturday in a renewed power struggle between the rival groups for control of <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>'s 1.2 million Shiites, the country's largest sect.
