geting certain ethnic grups. `` If the Klan is sincere in their endeavor and their efforts are to expose the drug dealers whether black, white or Hispanic, I commend them,'' he said. `` But if they are doing this to target certain ethnic groups, I think it is appalling and they should be punished without mercy and with passion.'' In <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>, a Klan group tried to join the state's `` Adopt-A-Highway'' program, an anti-litter campaign which credits volunteers who spruce up a section of highway by erecting a sign bearing their names In October, state <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Harrington </PERSON> denied the group's request.
