<HEAD>Child Strangled in Ski Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNISING, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> ski area shut down Tuesday after a 6-year-old boy apparently was strangled in a ski-lift mechanism. <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> <PERSON> Mazzali </PERSON> of <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Porte </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, visiting relatives with his parents, died Saturday at <LOCATION> Munising </LOCATION>'s city-owned <LOCATION> Maple </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mountain </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ski </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION> on <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Upper </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peninsula </LOCATION>, police Chief <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON> <PERSON> Miron </PERSON> said Tuesday. <PERSON> Don </PERSON> <PERSON> Fahrbach </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> Alger </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> medical examiner who handled boy's autopsy, said <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> apparently died of strangulation after his clothing became caught in the lift machinery. <PERSON> Fahrbach </PERSON> said tests to confirm the cause of death were due back later this week. <PERSON> Miron </PERSON> said it was the first time anyone had been killed or seriously injured at the ski hill. The resort, which is privately managed for the city, had been closed for Christmas and remained closed Tuesday, officials said.
