<HEAD>Farm Group Calls for Conference to Increase Food Aid to Eastern Europe</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Romania, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CORNING, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The leader of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farmers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> urged President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> and congressional leaders Tuesday to work with farmers to increase agricultural exports to <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>. `` Food will assist Eastern bloc nations more than dollars and, at the same time, help the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> agricultural economy,'' said <PERSON> DeVon </PERSON> <PERSON> Woodland </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Blackfoot </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, a rancher and president of the Iowa-based <ORGANIZATION> NFO </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Woodland </PERSON> said studies indicate that countries that received assistance under the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Food for Peace program have become friends of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and developed into trading partners. The same can not be said of countries receiving <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> financial aid, he said. `` Why dollar aid when people in the Eastern bloc countries have no food available to buy? We are the richest and most abundant agriculture country in the world. We should use this food to, or at least a portion of it, for assistance to the hungry,'' <PERSON> Woodland </PERSON> said in a statement released by <ORGANIZATION> NFO </ORGANIZATION> headquarters in <PERSON> Corning </PERSON>. The group represents more than 250,000 farm families and markets farm commodities for its members. Woodland said food shipments to <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> would reduce grain surpluses, and thereby push up the prices <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> farmers receive for their crops. He urged President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, Agriculture Secretary <PERSON> Clayton </PERSON> <PERSON> Yeutter </PERSON> and members of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> agriculture committees to consider establishing a federal agriculture conference to help increase exports of food to <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>.
